<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-08-31T04:34:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-08-31T04:34:00-05:00" n="662" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d662">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861a.01/67: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Harbin</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Jenkins</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-08-31T18:00:00+08:26"><hi rend="italic">August 31,
                                        1921—6 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received August 31—4:29
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Petroff, Chairman Council of Ministers Far Eastern Republic, and Kraajew
                            Nikoff [<hi rend="italic">Kozhevnikov</hi>], Assistant Secretary of
                            State, arrived in Harbin yesterday from Chita <hi rend="italic">en
                                route</hi> to Dairen where they expect to confer with Japanese.
                            Party had some difficulty with maritime customs but matter finally
                            arranged and they expect continue journey today. Legation informed.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Jenkins</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>